{"TopicId":168601,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"How to reassign trim button","CreatedByName":"Corona688","CreatedById":2511,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-12-16T17:31:32Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Corona688","CreatedById":2511,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-12-16T17:31:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSeriously, where is it?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rocket In My Pocket","CreatedById":154640,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-12-16T17:44:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223245893\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022168601\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221513445492\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u00222511\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Corona688\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 minutes ago, Corona688 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSeriously, where is it?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t think you can since it\u0027s just a modifier key?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, apparently there was a mod for this; which also makes me think it can\u0027t be done stock.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSadly, it looks pretty old. I doubt it works?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed5902770411\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/127318-12-trimplus-121-bind-trim-to-joystick-buttons-and-keyboard-keys/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:213px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Corona688","CreatedById":2511,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-12-16T17:48:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt doesn\u0027t look that old.\u00A0 Thanks.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rocket In My Pocket","CreatedById":154640,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-12-16T17:48:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFound this in the settings.cfg, it\u00A0might work also.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n}\u003Cbr\u003E\nMODIFIER_KEY\u003Cbr\u003E\n{\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0primary = LeftAlt\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0secondary = RightAlt\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0group = 0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0modeMask = -1\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0modeMaskSec = -1\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBe forewarned, this is going to change everything the Alt key does like the debug menu and such.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-12-16T17:48:59Z\u0022 title=\u002212/16/2017 05:48  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 16, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Rocket In My Pocket\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"GarrisonChisholm","CreatedById":146403,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-12-16T18:43:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n*looks stupidly back on the 100s of hours he\u0027s flown aircraft in KSP*\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\numm..., ...trim?\u00A0 0.0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Corona688","CreatedById":2511,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-12-16T18:53:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nalt-wasd, adds a tiny offset to pitch/roll/yaw.\u00A0 Notably, it does \u003Cstrong\u003Enot\u003C/strong\u003E do anything when \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E is on, so it\u0027s useless for some flying methods and indispensable for others.\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, alt-x kills all trim if you input any by accident.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"fourfa","CreatedById":151713,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-12-16T19:28:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt would be amazing if you could adjust trim with one\u00A0dial per axis on a joystick\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}